        embed_id: "a987a533-6b18-4880-a3bd-5a558895d3b2",
        type: "event",
        content: "type: event_result\nid: \"2442548\"\nprovider: resident_advisor\ntitle: Sanctum of Sound - June Edition\ndescription: \"Lineup: Nina Pixel, Robot Koch, Anahit Vardanyan, Jeena\\nGenres: Ambient, Experimental\\nSANCTUM OF SOUND IS A MUSICAL FORUM FOR LISTENERS OF AMBIENT, DEVOTIONAL, ELECTRONIC, EXPERIMENTAL AND PSYCHEDELIC MUSIC.\\n\\nCurated and produced by the MaHalla team, Sanctum of Sound takes place on the first Sunday of every month, transforming MaHalla into a sanctuary of music and sound for 8 immersive hours. Dedicated to the art of creation and transmission, it offers a space for deep listening and sonic exploration.\\n\\nThe next edition unfolds on Sunday, June 7th from 2 PM to 10 PM, featuring performances by Moriaariava & Nina Pixel, Anahit Vardanyan, The Four, Robot Koch and Jeena. \\n\\n__________________________________________________\\n\\nMoriaariava & Nina Pixel\\n\\nMoriaariava and Nina Pixel present ‘Snovanie’, their first live collaboration ever premiering within the Halls of MaHalla for Sanctum of Sound.\\n\\nNina Pixel is a sound artist, composer, and multidisciplinary creative researcher whose work investigates resonance, intuition, and collective imagination. Across performance, spatial sound works, participatory listening formats, and long-term research, her practice explores how sound shapes perception, time, and existing social fields.\\n\\nMoriaariava is a movement exploring what is immutable in the infinite space of the ever-manifesting experience. From compositions for piano, improvised instrumental conversations and spatial installations, to lyrically minimalist songs ‘from eternity for eternity’.\\n\\nBoth artists based in Berlin and of Slovakian origin move between different sound installations during the performance with instruments like the Guzheng, Piano, Harmonium, Gongs, Fujara and diverse arrangements including ancient melodies that people sang to synchronize when they worked in distant parts of hills and mountains.\\n\\n\\nRobot Koch\\n\\nAward-winning composer and immersive sound artist Robot Koch presents the Berlin premiere of his new album Quieter as part of his current international tour. \\nFollowing recent sold-out performances in the US, UK, and France, Robot Koch b...\"\nurl: \"https://ra.co/events/2442548\"\ndate_start: \"2026-06-07T14:00:00.000\"\ndate_end: \"2026-06-07T22:00:00.000\"\ntimezone: null\nevent_type: PHYSICAL\nvenue_name: MaHalla\nvenue_address: \"Wilhelminenhofstraße 76, 12459, Berlin\"\nvenue_city: Berlin\nvenue_state: null\nvenue_country: null\nvenue_lat: 52.458927\nvenue_lon: 13.523951\norganizer_name: Mahallla\norganizer_slug: null\norganizer_id: null\nrsvp_count: 25\nis_paid: true\nfee_amount: \"16.00\"\nfee_currency: EUR\nimage_url: \"https://images.ra.co/e8c0ed8f08bf461f26bdfd2867a4321aa20a2c38.jpg\"\nartists: Nina Pixel|Robot Koch|Anahit Vardanyan|Jeena\ngenres: Ambient|Experimental\nminimum_age: null\nis_festival: false\nhash: 2090a48413b76529\nembed_ref: sanctum-of-sound-vce\napp_id: events\nskill_id: search",
